    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE / 9200 9300 9400 MODELS BUILT AFTER JANUARY 1, 1995 - ELECTRONIC
        ENGINE CONTROLS - CUMMINS CELECT - 1992-1993 - TROUBLESHOOTING - BRAKE AND CLUTCH SWITCHES
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="8">
        <title>BRAKE AND CLUTCH SWITCHES</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title></title>
            <para>This test would be performed if the Electronic Service Tool (EST) displayed an incorrect switch
                position. For example:
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">The DDR displays either Clutch = RELEASED or DEPRESSED. The word "RELEASED" will appear
                    if the clutch pedal is in the released position (foot off the pedal) or "DEPRESSED" will appear when
                    the clutch pedal is depressed.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">The DDR displays either Service Brake = RELEASED or DEPRESSED. The word "RELEASED" will
                    appear when service brake pedal is not depressed and trailer hand valve is closed. The service brake
                    pressure switch will be closed allowing voltage to pass through the switch.
                </para>
                <para>The word "DEPRESSED" will appear when the brake pedal is depressed or the trailer hand valve is
                    open. The service brake pressure switch will be open, not allowing voltage to pass through the
                    switch.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <para>Refer to paragraphs
                <hotlnk document="s08143_6.xml" xrefid="x0814307">"Yellow" Engine Warning Light</hotlnk>
                and
                <hotlnk document="s08143_6.xml" xrefid="x0814308">"Red" Engine Stop Light</hotlnk>
                for operation description of clutch and brake switch.
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
